header.gameNote: KENT STATE TOURNAMENT AT KENT OH

article.headline: New Hampshire 65, Elon 64
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Jermaine Anderson's layup with two seconds left lifted New Hampshire to a 65-64 win over Elon in the first round of the Kent State Classic on Friday. New Hampshire (3-8) led by as many as 11 points with 3:28 left in the first half, but Elon closed the gap to 34-27 at halftime and kept the score within five points throughout the second period. Elon (2-8) then tied the game at 59-59 when LeVonn Jordan made a foul shot with 2:10 left to play, then took a 62-59 lead on Chris Chalko's 3-pointer. With the Phoenix clinging to a 64-63 lead, Elon's Brian Waters missed a free throw with 10 seconds left. Tyrece Gibbs got the rebound for New Hampshire, which drove the court and scored the winning basket on Anderson's layup. Jordan scored 19 points and had seven rebounds for Elon, and Waters added 15 points. New Hampshire's Blagoj Janev led all scorers with 22. Mike Christensen had 15 points and Gibbs added 10 points and eight rebounds for the Wildcats.
